WEBVTT

00:11.887 --> 00:13.722
<i>It was the first day
of senior year,</i>

00:13.847 --> 00:15.724
<i>and I woke up still drunk.</i>

00:16.099 --> 00:18.477
<i>The night before was mostly a blur.</i>

00:19.019 --> 00:21.813
<i>That is,
after I emptied out the entire minibar.</i>

00:21.980 --> 00:24.066
<i>If I had any chance of making it
through the day,</i>

00:24.149 --> 00:26.193
<i>I needed something to soak up the booze.</i>

00:26.818 --> 00:28.487
<i>"Went to Atlanta for AA retreat.</i>

00:28.946 --> 00:33.200
<i>Unreachable for four days.
Call if you need me. Smiley face, Mom.</i>

00:33.700 --> 00:34.785
<i>First day of school.</i>

00:35.327 --> 00:36.161
<i>Good job, Mom.</i>

00:36.870 --> 00:39.164
<i>But, with no mom, I could ditch.</i>

00:39.623 --> 00:42.793
<i>If I was gonna be a beauty queen,
only one teacher mattered.</i>

00:45.879 --> 00:48.382
I thought Magnolia wanted me
to coach her.

00:48.465 --> 00:50.509
I had no idea she wanted to seduce me.

00:50.592 --> 00:53.220
Well, you never should have put yourself
in that position.

00:53.303 --> 00:56.932
No grown man should have to jump
out of a teenage girl's window.

00:57.015 --> 00:58.475
We should tell her parents.

00:59.142 --> 01:00.978
If it were our daughter, I'd want to know.

01:01.061 --> 01:04.188
Are you insane?
You're an accused child molester.

01:04.897 --> 01:06.400
Plus, If you tell the Barnards,

01:06.483 --> 01:08.902
Etta Mae will never sponsor me
for Junior League.

01:08.986 --> 01:10.362
Heaven forbid.

01:10.862 --> 01:13.448
Please, Bob, no more coaching. Okay?

01:13.532 --> 01:18.495
Just focus on your legal career
with clients who are over 18.

01:18.579 --> 01:20.622
That blonde girl was a catastrophe.

01:20.789 --> 01:23.041
Showing up
at our gala looking like a whore.

01:23.125 --> 01:25.085
We are still working on Patty's look.

01:25.168 --> 01:26.753
No, we are not.

01:27.087 --> 01:28.630
Leave it alone.

01:29.673 --> 01:31.258
<i>Except I couldn't.</i>

01:31.425 --> 01:35.220
<i>Patty was my chance
to get my pageant coaching mojo back.</i>

01:35.679 --> 01:38.181
<i>I'd just have to keep things
on the down low.</i>

01:40.000 --> 01:46.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:47.357 --> 01:49.318
I'm here.
I'm ready for you to make me a winner.

01:49.735 --> 01:51.486
And I brought donuts,
breakfast of champions.

01:51.570 --> 01:54.323
- Jesus, what happened to you?
- Nothing.

01:55.032 --> 01:57.784
Uh... I'm a little hungover.

01:57.868 --> 01:59.494
You... were drinking?

01:59.578 --> 02:03.040
Today is your first day of school.
You need to be fresh, alert.

02:03.290 --> 02:06.043
I'm not going.
Beauty queens don't need school.

02:06.418 --> 02:09.170
Okay. When is the last time
you heard of a beauty queen

02:09.253 --> 02:12.174
slash high school dropout
slash blackout drunk?

02:12.257 --> 02:13.800
Does your mom know you're here?

02:14.176 --> 02:17.512
She's out of town,
so I guess you're in charge of me now.

02:17.846 --> 02:18.972
Can I call you daddy?

02:19.222 --> 02:20.432
Absolutely not.

02:24.144 --> 02:25.854
What is that?

02:26.271 --> 02:27.230
Makeup caboodle.

02:27.314 --> 02:29.900
Let's get you cleaned up
and I'll take you to school.

02:30.609 --> 02:32.736
No. I haven't even eaten anything yet.

02:34.988 --> 02:36.907
Hey, give that back. I'm starving.

02:37.407 --> 02:38.241
Good.

02:38.825 --> 02:40.827
Maybe your body will start eating itself.

02:50.796 --> 02:52.589
I'm not ever going back there again.

02:54.966 --> 02:56.093
You want to talk about it?

03:05.644 --> 03:10.482
<i>Dear Blob Armstrong, you're fat!</i>

03:10.857 --> 03:11.983
Wow.

03:13.235 --> 03:14.069
You <i>were </i> fat.

03:15.112 --> 03:16.530
Until I wasn't.

03:17.364 --> 03:19.908
It gets better. I promise.

03:20.534 --> 03:23.787
Trust me, skinny is magic.

03:24.037 --> 03:25.997
You are not Fatty Patty anymore.

03:26.289 --> 03:27.624
So who am I, then?

03:28.041 --> 03:29.626
Whoever you wanna be.

03:29.918 --> 03:33.588
Today is the day
we write your pageant narrative,

03:33.672 --> 03:36.383
the story that you will tell
on the pageant stage.

03:36.633 --> 03:39.386
Who you are and why they should pick you.

03:39.469 --> 03:43.849
You can be the former fatty
turned class president,

03:43.932 --> 03:47.853
or cheerleader, or homecoming queen.

03:47.936 --> 03:49.896
You are a blank slate.

03:49.980 --> 03:53.024
So, let's make you a pretty picture.

03:57.988 --> 03:58.822
Uh-oh.

03:59.531 --> 04:01.241
I feel a makeover coming on.

04:12.961 --> 04:14.379
<i>Maybe Bob was right.</i>

04:14.546 --> 04:16.673
<i>I could write a whole new story.</i>

04:17.257 --> 04:18.716
<i>I felt like Cinderella,</i>

04:18.800 --> 04:22.387
<i>and there was my Prince Charming,
Brick Armstrong.</i>

04:22.471 --> 04:24.765
<i>Maybe my pageant narrative could be
like a fairy tale,</i>

04:24.848 --> 04:28.018
<i>where the vengeful maiden
rejects the hero, like he did to me.</i>

04:28.560 --> 04:29.394
Brick.

04:34.524 --> 04:35.901
Hey, babe.

04:36.693 --> 04:37.527
Patty.

04:37.986 --> 04:39.279
<i>So much for revenge.</i>

04:39.362 --> 04:40.781
You guys know each other?

04:41.281 --> 04:43.200
That's Patty Bladell.

04:43.742 --> 04:46.870
No way. Uh, Fatty Patty's huge.

04:48.455 --> 04:50.081
Just because you're skinny now

04:50.165 --> 04:52.626
doesn't mean you can steal
someone else's boyfriend.

04:53.251 --> 04:54.169
Got it?

04:56.880 --> 04:59.007
Oh, my God, that was sick.

04:59.466 --> 05:02.469
Magnolia Barnard was just totally
threatened by you.

05:02.594 --> 05:04.930
Oh, this is like every great
high school movie ever made.

05:05.013 --> 05:07.349
Geek turned chic. Mm-hmm?

05:07.432 --> 05:09.684
Is this the part where you dump me
for better friends

05:09.768 --> 05:11.770
and start sleeping with all the hot guys?

05:11.853 --> 05:12.687
Or girls?

05:12.938 --> 05:15.857
No, we are definitely not in that movie.

05:15.941 --> 05:16.858
Good.

05:16.983 --> 05:20.278
So, now... I <i>am </i> your boyfriend?

05:20.362 --> 05:22.864
'Cause last night,
you said you weren't sure.

05:23.031 --> 05:24.908
I'm not, but until I decide,

05:24.991 --> 05:26.827
I'm not letting you flirt
with some other girl.

05:26.910 --> 05:30.205
So, no other girls, got it.

05:30.288 --> 05:31.915
Brick, is there someone else?

05:31.998 --> 05:32.916
No way.

05:33.834 --> 05:34.668
I love you.

05:37.087 --> 05:39.881
Okay, that is literally the first time
you've ever said that to me.

05:40.674 --> 05:42.801
- Why'd it take you so long?
- I don't know.

05:44.261 --> 05:45.262
Maybe I was scared.

05:45.345 --> 05:47.722
I haven't said that to anyone before,
except for my mom.

05:58.108 --> 06:01.611
<i>For the first time in my life,
I was pure potential.</i>

06:01.736 --> 06:03.738
<i>The world was my oyster.</i>

06:03.947 --> 06:06.783
<i>I could be the former fatty
who turned into a brain.</i>

06:06.992 --> 06:08.618
<i>Or an athlete.</i>

06:09.286 --> 06:10.412
<i>Or a basket case.</i>

06:11.621 --> 06:12.998
<i>Or a princess.</i>

06:15.250 --> 06:16.459
<i>Or a criminal.</i>

06:16.543 --> 06:18.920
<i>Well, obviously, not a criminal.</i>

06:25.427 --> 06:27.304
We're discussing today's news.

06:27.596 --> 06:28.597
Mm-hmm?

06:28.972 --> 06:31.349
Some guy almost died in a fire
at the Halfway Inn.

06:33.894 --> 06:34.811
What hotel?

06:35.145 --> 06:37.063
The one by the freeway.
Halfway Inn.

06:37.147 --> 06:38.773
Guy's in, like, critical condition.

06:39.566 --> 06:41.651
<i>Oh, my God. Was I criminal?</i>

06:43.361 --> 06:48.617
<i>Could it be possible
that I am becoming a killer?</i>

06:49.284 --> 06:52.203
We need to go to the bathroom. Together.

06:53.496 --> 06:54.998
- Together.
- Together.

06:58.376 --> 07:00.670
I was at that motel last night,
with the homeless guy.

07:00.754 --> 07:02.464
Thank God you missed the fire.

07:02.714 --> 07:03.632
Totally.

07:03.840 --> 07:05.675
- Unless I didn't.
- What are you talking about?

07:06.927 --> 07:08.720
You know how I was gonna bang him,

07:08.803 --> 07:11.097
and then, I didn't,
so I still wanted revenge?

07:11.181 --> 07:13.016
Patty, what did you do?

07:13.308 --> 07:17.812
I may have briefly considered
lighting him on fire.

07:17.938 --> 07:19.648
Patty, are you insane?

07:19.731 --> 07:20.815
I don't know.

07:20.899 --> 07:23.568
I cleaned out the minibar,
I watched <i>Firestarter. </i> The rest is a blur.

07:23.652 --> 07:26.154
Wait, you watched <i>Firestarter</i> without me?

07:26.571 --> 07:27.572
I can't believe you.

07:27.656 --> 07:28.573
Nonnie!

07:29.032 --> 07:31.326
What if I got drunk
and set the guy on fire?

07:31.409 --> 07:32.285
What if he dies?

07:32.369 --> 07:34.621
Okay, okay.
Let's think about this logically.

07:34.704 --> 07:36.414
There's someone in critical condition,

07:36.498 --> 07:38.375
but we don't know
if it's your homeless guy.

07:38.458 --> 07:39.417
Yeah, totally.

07:39.501 --> 07:42.003
You... You really think
that it could be just a coincidence?

07:42.295 --> 07:44.881
That I thought
about lighting a guy on fire,

07:44.965 --> 07:46.967
and then a different guy was in a fire

07:47.050 --> 07:49.219
at the motel where I thought
about lighting a guy on fire,

07:49.302 --> 07:51.596
but it was a different guy
and a different fire?

07:51.888 --> 07:53.014
It's possible.

07:53.098 --> 07:54.349
- Yeah.
- I'll ditch,

07:54.432 --> 07:56.393
go to the hospital, and find out.

07:56.476 --> 07:57.727
You should stay here.

07:57.811 --> 08:00.230
My dad says the easiest way
to catch a murderer is to see

08:00.313 --> 08:01.564
who comes to visit the victim.

08:02.023 --> 08:04.526
- I'm a murderer?
- Only if he dies.

08:06.361 --> 08:08.571
Nonnie, what am I supposed to do?
Just wait around?

08:08.655 --> 08:10.031
Go to class. Blend.

08:10.115 --> 08:13.493
Pretend you're a normal teenager.
Who knows, you actually might be.

08:14.119 --> 08:15.286
I'll text you later.

08:22.794 --> 08:24.254
Bob, hi.

08:24.879 --> 08:27.799
I didn't expect to see you at home.
I came to see Etta Mae.

08:27.882 --> 08:29.050
Etta Mae's out of town.

08:29.217 --> 08:31.594
Another surgery.
Separating conjoined twins.

08:31.678 --> 08:33.096
You must be so proud.

08:33.179 --> 08:34.764
If I only had the time.

08:34.847 --> 08:37.600
Look, I'm already an hour late for work,
and I'm out of fresh shirts.

08:37.892 --> 08:41.395
Oh, well, I could press a shirt for you.
I could straighten up the house, too.

08:41.479 --> 08:44.149
Now, why on God's green earth
would you do that?

08:44.232 --> 08:46.359
Well, it's the neighborly thing to do,

08:46.443 --> 08:50.697
and I'm sure Etta Mae would appreciate
knowing that you are well cared for.

08:50.780 --> 08:53.950
Well, well, that's awfully nice of you.
Come on in.

08:54.200 --> 08:56.411
Just don't judge, okay?
The house is a mess.

09:02.333 --> 09:03.543
<i>I was anxious.</i>

09:03.626 --> 09:05.920
<i>Stressed. Paralyzed with fear.</i>

09:06.004 --> 09:08.548
<i>Sure, I was scared I might be
a murdering arsonist,</i>

09:08.631 --> 09:12.177
<i>but that was nothing compared
to facing a high school cafeteria.</i>

09:12.510 --> 09:14.512
<i>Nonnie told me to blend in.</i>

09:14.679 --> 09:16.222
<i>Be inconspicuous.</i>

09:16.973 --> 09:19.309
<i>I was used to being invisible.</i>

09:19.392 --> 09:21.394
<i>I needed to find a place to hide out.</i>

09:21.561 --> 09:26.274
<i>A group of kids nobody cared about,
but not with those sadists from the band.</i>

09:43.041 --> 09:44.375
Oh!

09:44.834 --> 09:46.044
<i>Maybe the stoners.</i>

09:46.127 --> 09:48.963
<i>Maybe this time they'd be too baked
to even notice me.</i>

09:50.965 --> 09:52.050
Watch it, Patty.

09:52.425 --> 09:53.468
Sorry.

09:54.636 --> 09:58.640
You know what rhymes with Patty?
Fatty. Fatty Patty!

09:58.723 --> 10:00.475
<i>I wasn't Fatty Patty anymore.</i>

10:00.558 --> 10:03.353
<i>I needed to find a place
where the new me fit in.</i>

10:08.066 --> 10:09.651
Yes, you, come here.

10:09.734 --> 10:14.114
<i>For the first time in my life,
could I actually be popular?</i>

10:14.614 --> 10:17.534
<i>I couldn't go to jail.
I finally get to sit at the cool table.</i>

10:17.617 --> 10:18.868
So are you new?

10:19.744 --> 10:22.413
Uh, definitely on the outside.

10:22.622 --> 10:23.957
Welcome to Masonville.

10:25.750 --> 10:27.627
Hey, Alicia, have you met, um...

10:32.674 --> 10:33.842
I'm sorry, who are you?

10:35.301 --> 10:36.553
I don't know.

10:37.720 --> 10:38.930
Excuse me.

10:41.015 --> 10:43.977
<i>Maybe everybody else had forgotten
about Fatty Patty,</i>

10:44.060 --> 10:45.562
<i>but I couldn't let her go.</i>

10:45.854 --> 10:47.772
So, I have to go.

10:47.856 --> 10:49.816
- I just got called in on a case.
- Ah.

10:49.899 --> 10:51.025
A personal favor.

10:51.860 --> 10:53.027
Okay.

10:53.278 --> 10:56.614
So should I lock up when I leave, then,
or what?

10:56.698 --> 10:57.991
- Yeah, sounds good.
- Okay.

10:58.074 --> 11:00.994
If you need me to return the favor,
don't hesitate to ask.

11:01.661 --> 11:04.038
- Oh.
- Thanks, Coralee, you're a real peach.

11:04.664 --> 11:05.915
Ah.

11:07.125 --> 11:09.544
Uh...

11:09.711 --> 11:11.588
- Have a good one.
- All right.

11:52.003 --> 11:52.962
Regina?

12:25.578 --> 12:26.955
- Hi.
- Hi.

12:27.038 --> 12:31.084
I'm here with Masonville High's
Caring for a Cause Alliance,

12:31.167 --> 12:34.212
and we heard there was a guy
in a fire who's in the ICU.

12:34.295 --> 12:37.090
- I brought him a little something.
- Yeah, straight ahead. Room 102.

12:37.173 --> 12:38.216
Thank you.

12:47.100 --> 12:48.351
Nonnie?

12:52.063 --> 12:53.106
Dad.

12:53.189 --> 12:55.233
Everything okay?
Why aren't you in school?

12:55.316 --> 12:57.986
Yeah, I'm just here doing research
for an assignment.

12:58.278 --> 12:59.946
- You?
- Official police business.

13:00.029 --> 13:01.781
There was a fire,
and it's looking like arson.

13:02.073 --> 13:03.199
Arson?

13:03.283 --> 13:05.785
There's a guy who got caught in it.
Bad liver, weak heart.

13:05.868 --> 13:07.578
With that smoke inhalation,
he could die,

13:07.662 --> 13:09.372
which would make this a homicide.

13:09.455 --> 13:10.957
My first ever.

13:11.040 --> 13:11.874
Awesome, right?

13:12.125 --> 13:13.751
Not for the dead guy.

13:13.835 --> 13:16.337
Oh, yeah, no, no. No, no, of course. Uh...

13:16.421 --> 13:18.381
You gotta admit, I mean, it's pretty cool.

13:18.506 --> 13:22.427
- Nothing ever happens in this town.
- So, do you guys have any suspects?

13:22.510 --> 13:25.930
Not officially. He was with a girl.
Night clerk saw them check in together.

13:27.348 --> 13:29.892
- Do you have a description of her?
- Sorry.

13:30.101 --> 13:33.187
Can't say any more
without compromising the investigation.

13:45.325 --> 13:48.077
So, I'm new. Are you?

13:48.369 --> 13:49.245
Uh...

13:51.080 --> 13:51.956
No.

13:52.040 --> 13:54.959
Why are you sitting alone?
You steal somebody's boyfriend?

13:56.502 --> 13:57.587
Girlfriend?

13:57.670 --> 14:00.173
- Why did you think that I would...
- 'Cause I know how things work.

14:00.381 --> 14:02.383
If a girl as hot as you is sitting alone,

14:03.009 --> 14:05.386
she's new or a social pariah.

14:06.012 --> 14:10.099
<i>Did the hottest guy I've ever seen
besides Brick Armstrong just call me hot?</i>

14:10.183 --> 14:13.102
So what happened? Did you, like,
light someone on fire or something?

14:14.270 --> 14:15.146
I'm Christian.

14:15.688 --> 14:19.650
That's my name and my religion,
which is super annoying and on the nose,

14:19.734 --> 14:22.779
but... my dad's a preacher

14:23.196 --> 14:24.238
and a missionary,

14:24.322 --> 14:26.115
hence I've been
to five different high schools.

14:27.700 --> 14:29.535
This is the part
where you tell me your name.

14:30.203 --> 14:31.120
And your backstory.

14:31.204 --> 14:32.246
I'm Patty.

14:33.122 --> 14:34.040
No backstory.

14:34.123 --> 14:36.376
I like a woman of mystery.

14:39.337 --> 14:41.798
<i>I'd never been a woman of mystery
in my life,</i>

14:41.881 --> 14:43.299
<i>but I wasn't about to tell him that.</i>

14:44.842 --> 14:46.636
Why do you need to get a lawyer?

14:56.854 --> 14:58.231
You are so fucked.

14:58.314 --> 15:01.818
Ooh, is this one
of those afternoon delight kinda visits?

15:01.901 --> 15:03.027
In the bad way.

15:03.236 --> 15:05.113
Regina had you followed.

15:05.363 --> 15:07.490
Where in the hell did you get these?

15:07.573 --> 15:10.159
You better tell Barnard the truth
and get out in front of it.

15:10.243 --> 15:12.495
I wanted to do that this morning.

15:12.578 --> 15:14.163
You made me promise not to.

15:14.497 --> 15:17.875
It's too late. If I tell him now,
it's gonna seem like I'm covering.

15:17.959 --> 15:19.293
We gotta figure out another way.

15:19.377 --> 15:20.753
Well, you need to figure it out.

15:20.837 --> 15:23.840
I'm not the one who can't stay away
from teenage girls.

15:28.052 --> 15:29.053
Oh.

15:30.888 --> 15:33.433
I should probably pick that up.
It could be an emergency.

15:33.891 --> 15:34.809
About what?

15:34.892 --> 15:37.186
Her first day of school.
She was really scared.

15:37.270 --> 15:38.688
And how do you know that?

15:38.771 --> 15:42.108
Because... I saw her this morning.
I gave her a makeover.

15:42.191 --> 15:44.986
My God, Bob! You are pathological.

15:45.403 --> 15:49.615
Please, please, no more Patty, okay?
There is something off about that girl.

15:49.699 --> 15:52.034
I am telling you, you are wrong.

15:52.118 --> 15:52.994
Hello?

15:53.077 --> 15:54.912
<i>I think I may have killed someone.</i>

15:55.371 --> 15:56.664
I gotta go.

15:57.748 --> 15:59.792
My life just started.

15:59.917 --> 16:02.462
I... I don't want it to be over already.

16:08.926 --> 16:10.428
I'm a horrible person.

16:10.511 --> 16:11.596
You're not.

16:12.972 --> 16:14.223
I wanted to hurt him.

16:14.640 --> 16:18.478
<i>I had to do something.
She was ruining my $1,500 jacket.</i>

16:18.561 --> 16:21.564
- Listen to me, Patty.
- Mm-hmm?

16:21.647 --> 16:24.901
Having a murderous thought is not the same
as having murderous intent.

16:24.984 --> 16:26.194
That is not who you are.

16:27.695 --> 16:28.571
How do you know?

16:28.654 --> 16:32.450
Because I see you.
Because I see what's really in your heart.

16:32.533 --> 16:33.576
I saw it first.

16:36.746 --> 16:39.415
We are gonna prove
you didn't do this, together.

16:40.541 --> 16:41.834
All of us.

16:43.628 --> 16:45.755
You, we've got to jog your memory, hmm?

16:45.838 --> 16:46.714
I need you to go back

16:46.797 --> 16:49.467
and mentally retrace your steps
from last night.

16:49.550 --> 16:51.636
Maybe you can fill in the blanks,

16:51.719 --> 16:53.596
remember something
that'll let you off the hook.

16:53.679 --> 16:56.474
But stay away from the motel, hmm?

16:57.433 --> 16:58.768
And stay out of trouble.

16:58.976 --> 16:59.852
Got it?

