32:23.150 --> 32:24.317
Literally.

32:24.484 --> 32:27.779
Go back in there, lure your father out.
I'll take care of her.

32:28.613 --> 32:29.948
- Patty.
- Bob.

32:30.031 --> 32:32.367
Go back to the ER, now.

32:34.202 --> 32:35.370
That's her.

32:36.288 --> 32:38.290
That's the girl I was with last night.

32:38.373 --> 32:39.666
She started the fire.

32:41.084 --> 32:42.210
Patty?

32:43.253 --> 32:44.588
You better come in here.

32:48.049 --> 32:49.968
Were you with this man
at the motel last night?

32:50.927 --> 32:52.012
Tell him, blondie.

32:53.180 --> 32:54.848
I'm Ms. Bladell's attorney.

32:54.931 --> 32:56.558
I would like to postpone any questioning

32:56.641 --> 32:59.311
until my client
and I have a chance to confer.

32:59.853 --> 33:01.605
Confer about what? She did it.

33:03.231 --> 33:04.816
<i>Couldn't be true.</i>

33:04.900 --> 33:06.860
<i>For me or for her.</i>

33:08.111 --> 33:09.863
<i>I was grasping at straws.</i>

33:13.325 --> 33:16.161
<i>Suddenly, I knew what I was looking for.</i>

33:17.621 --> 33:20.457
Hey, what are you doin'?
Stop touching my stuff.

33:20.540 --> 33:22.542
Were you wearing these clothes
the night of the fire?

33:22.751 --> 33:24.961
- Yeah, but...
- Ah!

33:25.378 --> 33:28.924
I think we both know what really happened,
homeless guy.

33:29.466 --> 33:31.343
My name is John.

33:32.010 --> 33:33.053
Hey.

33:33.720 --> 33:37.349
You woke up, drunk, alone,

33:38.141 --> 33:41.019
your clothes in the bed,
soaked in spilled liquor.

33:41.102 --> 33:43.438
Just another day
in the life of a derelict.

33:43.688 --> 33:48.443
And then, creature of habit,
you reached for a cigarette.

33:48.985 --> 33:50.612
But before you could light it,

33:50.695 --> 33:53.532
you looked up
and saw a smoke alarm above the bed.

33:53.823 --> 33:57.494
But you weren't gonna let that stop you.
You decided to disarm it.

33:57.577 --> 33:58.453
You jumped up...

33:59.746 --> 34:02.666
and you removed the battery,
slipping it into your pocket.

34:02.749 --> 34:08.755
And then, you lit your cigarette,
dropping a match to the bed.

34:11.466 --> 34:15.136
You jumped off the bed,
ran to the bathroom to escape the flames,

34:15.219 --> 34:17.931
but you ran into the doorjamb
and knocked yourself unconscious.

34:28.608 --> 34:30.110
And then, you lied...

34:31.069 --> 34:34.822
and blamed Patty
so you didn't get in trouble...

34:35.322 --> 34:36.741
for starting the fire.

34:37.242 --> 34:39.077
How could you know all that?

34:39.619 --> 34:40.829
Were you in the closet?

34:40.911 --> 34:42.455
That sounds like a confession.

34:43.665 --> 34:45.000
Oh, fuck it.

34:45.166 --> 34:47.043
Yeah, it was me.

34:49.045 --> 34:51.422
<i>Because of Bob, I had a future.</i>

34:51.590 --> 34:53.341
<i>There was hope for a new me.</i>

34:53.425 --> 34:55.885
<i>My pageant story wasn't over yet.</i>

34:56.011 --> 34:57.012
I'm not a monster.

34:57.094 --> 34:59.639
No, you're my great white hope.

35:00.056 --> 35:02.892
That... sounds a little racist.

35:04.269 --> 35:06.980
We are gonna do amazing things.

35:08.481 --> 35:09.316
Bukkake.

35:10.483 --> 35:13.695
Okay. Let's get to the bottom of this.

35:13.778 --> 35:16.281
Already done, Bob.

35:16.364 --> 35:17.824
Already done.

35:19.951 --> 35:22.746
I gotta go home.
My son's been in a fender bender.

35:23.371 --> 35:24.372
Texting and driving.

35:24.456 --> 35:27.292
Nonnie, can you make sure
Patty gets discharged and get her home?

35:27.459 --> 35:29.669
Yeah, I'm always there for her.

35:29.794 --> 35:32.255
And never say "discharge."

35:33.798 --> 35:37.344
We're gonna start coaching this weekend.
You get home and go straight to bed.

35:37.427 --> 35:40.013
- Think you can handle that?
- Mm-hmm.

35:40.096 --> 35:42.849
Um... thank you for saving me.

35:44.017 --> 35:45.268
What about me?

35:49.230 --> 35:51.691
So much for the first day of senior year.

35:51.941 --> 35:53.526
We'll have a do-over tomorrow.

35:53.610 --> 35:55.070
Put this all behind us.

35:57.614 --> 35:59.616
<i>But I couldn't put it behind me.</i>

35:59.699 --> 36:00.784
<i>Not yet.</i>

36:01.159 --> 36:02.952
<i>There was one more thing I had to do.</i>

36:03.036 --> 36:04.120
I'll be right back.

36:04.788 --> 36:06.581
Wait, where are you going?

36:07.666 --> 36:08.500
Patty.

36:11.211 --> 36:14.172
Just so you know,
I'm the fatty you punched.

36:14.673 --> 36:15.715
You broke my jaw.

36:16.216 --> 36:18.593
I couldn't eat solid food
for three months.

36:19.386 --> 36:20.887
So you owe me an apology.

36:21.304 --> 36:22.681
An... an apology?

36:23.348 --> 36:24.891
You should be thanking me.

36:25.392 --> 36:28.144
I saved you.
Because of me, you got skinny.

36:28.770 --> 36:31.189
Skinny isn't magic.

36:32.107 --> 36:35.485
It doesn't take away all of the years
that I got treated like shit.

36:35.568 --> 36:37.529
- Well, let it go.
- I can't!

36:38.571 --> 36:43.201
I might be skinny on the outside,
but on the inside, I'm still Fatty Patty.

36:43.284 --> 36:47.414
- That's pathetic.
- Oh, I want you to hurt, like I hurt.

36:47.831 --> 36:50.583
You deserve it.
I wish I had lit your ass on fire.

36:50.709 --> 36:52.877
I hope you drop fucking dead.

36:59.718 --> 37:03.805
<i>I wanted him dead,
and then he was.</i>

37:04.389 --> 37:06.641
<i>And I... was happy.</i>

37:08.059 --> 37:10.061
<i>Did that make me a horrible person?</i>

37:10.437 --> 37:13.314
<i>Did it make me responsible?</i>

37:14.607 --> 37:18.194
<i>Maybe Bob was right.
Maybe skinny </i> was <i>magic.</i>

37:20.613 --> 37:22.490
<i>I wondered what else I could do.</i>

